citations:
    citation-adwd-the-queens-hand:
        source: source-adwd
        properties:
            locator: "The Queen's Hand"
            text_from_source: "The Dornish prince was three days dying. He took his last shuddering breath in the bleak black dawn, as cold rain hissed from a dark sky to turn the brick streets of the old city into rivers."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Barristan Selmy POV. Set three days after the Dragontamer chapter. Quentyn Martell dies just before dawn — his face is barely recognizable, skull showing through sloughed flesh, eyes pools of pus. Missandei had nursed him through his dying. Rhaegal has made his lair atop the pyramid of Hazkar (now a smoldering ruin from dragonfire); Viserion occupies the pyramid of Yherizan. Both dragons freed by Quentyn's botched theft. Barristan has assumed the title Queen's Hand in Daenerys's absence. Skahaz mo Kandaq (the Shavepate) serves as chief military advisor wearing a wolf's-head mask. Council of war held around a round table: Marselen (Mother's Men), Symon Stripeback (Free Brothers), Tal Toraq (Stalwart Shields), Grey Worm (Unsullied), Jokin and the Widower (Stormcrows), Rommo (Dothraki), pit fighters Goghor, Belaquo, Camarron, and the Spotted Cat; Strong Belwas attends (still weakened from the poisoned locusts). 29+ Sons of the Harpy murders in one night. Hizdahr zo Loraq is imprisoned ('in chains'). Barristan has sent Galazza Galare (the Green Grace) to the Yunkai'i to negotiate ransom of hostages (Daario Naharis, Jhogo, Hero). Barristan orders a beacon fire to be prepared atop the Great Pyramid as a signal for a coordinated attack. He plans to break the siege — 'fire and blood.' Archibald Yronwood and Gerris Drinkwater are held in a cell. Barristan tells them their prince is dead and asks for their swords in exchange for safe passage home to Dorne with Quentyn's bones. The Dornishmen confirm the Tattered Prince demanded Pentos as his price for assisting Quentyn. Ser Archibald used his burned hands to beat out the flames consuming Quentyn after the attack."
